EmailTemplate.textOnly:
<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" />
Dear {!Contact.Name},
Thank you for your interest in joining CASS {!Case.Country__c}.
In order for us to initiate your application process, please find below a summary of the documentation to be submitted to IATA:
- IATA CASS Airline Participation Details Form: Please complete the form in electronic typewritten format (i.e. not handwritten) with all the information requested, and then sign and certify it with your Companys official stamp.
- Bank Account Mandate: For settlement purposes the airline must provide IATA with a Banking Mandate for each CASS country:
The mandate can be provided in two forms: Local bank account in the CASS Country and Currency or IATA Currency Clearance Service (ICCS) contract for cross border payments instructions For more information on ICCS please visit http://www.iata.org/services/finance/iccs/Pages/index.aspx If you would like to use a local bank account, please note that the corresponding mandate must be issued as per the attached instructions and template, and signed at your Airline Head Office by two senior officers. At least one of which must be:
o Chief Financial Officer (CFO) or o Head of Treasury or Cash Management Department
The process will begin once all original documents are received at the Geneva Head Office at the below address:
Global Airline Participation Team International Air Transport Association 33, Route de l'Aroport 1215 Geneva 15 Airport Switzerland Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber}
Fees:
Joining Fee is USD 2,500.00 per CASS Country. Advance payment required. Other fees: as per IATA Cargo Services Price List
Thank you,
{!Case.OwnerFullName}
Global Airline Participation Team
Industry Distribution and Financial Services
International Air Transport Association
33, Route de l'Aroport
1215 Geneva 15 Airport
Switzerland
www.iata.org/customer
